Warchlinko  (formerly German Klein Wachlin) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Stargard, within Stargard County, West Pomeranian Voivodeship, in north-western Poland. It lies approximately  north of Stargard and  east of the regional capital Szczecin.
For the history of the region, see History of Pomerania.
